    "narrative": "Gunnar Henderson leads the charge today with an elite 81.17 score, buoyed by a favorable matchup against Shane Smith. Beyond the raw projection, Henderson\u2019s value is maximized by a 14% platoon edge and, crucially, a slow opposing delivery that significantly bolsters his stolen base upside\u2014the primary currency of our strategy. Josh Lowe (72.21) and Nolan Schanuel (67.16) also represent high-leverage starts; both benefit from a prime matchup against Reynaldo L\u00f3pez, whose 6.36 xERA invites aggressive deployment. While L\u00f3pez is a weak arm, we are monitoring Lowe closely, as his position in the seven-hole slightly suppresses his run-production ceiling compared to the top-of-the-order anchors.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved Marcell Ozuna (52.61), who narrowly missed the cut behind the utility slot occupied by Vladimir Guerrero Jr. (52.89). While Ozuna\u2019s 8% BvP edge against Nick Pivetta was compelling, Guerrero\u2019s superior underlying xwOBA (.384) ultimately tipped the scales. We are proceeding with caution regarding the OF-heavy lineup: Luis Robert Jr. (45.68) carries a significant risk profile today, as his 15% platoon disadvantage is compounded by adverse wind conditions, potentially pulling him below our efficiency floor if the early innings suggest a struggle against Zac Gallen. All projections remain contingent on lineup confirmation; should any \"Pending\" status shift downward in the batting order, we will pivot to protect our game caps accordingly.",
